Package com.pranab.playwithgraphs.weightedgraphs

Interface WeightedGraph<V,​K,​W extends Weight>

Type Parameters:
V - The relational entity type, that will be used as vertex in vertex-edge mapping ,
K - Unique key to identify a Vertex
W - An entity that implements Weight so as to simulate strength of relationship as integer values.
All Superinterfaces:
Graph<V,​K>
All Known Subinterfaces:
DirectedWeightedGraph<V,​K,​W>, UnDirectedWeightedGraph<V,​K,​W>
All Known Implementing Classes:
AdjacencyListDirectedWeightedGraph, AdjancencyListUnDirectedWeightedGraph
public interface WeightedGraph<V,​K,​W extends Weight>
extends Graph<V,​K>
An Object that helps in realization of data in Vertex Edge(Graph) format.

Vertex : The entity that is to be related with another entity.

Edge : Relationship between the entities.

Weighted Graph Definition: A set of items connected by edges. Each item is called a vertex or node. Formally, a graph is a set of vertices and a binary relation between vertices, adjacency. Graph is considered to be weighted when the relationship between nodes have varying strength or lenghts.

Author:
Pranab Bharadwaj
